00:02.360 --> 00:04.220
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05.700 --> 00:07.669
Will you offer a
prayer for my soul

00:07.670 --> 00:10.669
as you stand over my corpse
and confirm my passing?

00:10.670 --> 00:13.859
Oh, I shall.

00:13.860 --> 00:15.599
That is Samuel Drummond.

00:15.600 --> 00:16.679
His friends call him Drum.

00:16.680 --> 00:18.039
And that is Francis Thatcher.

00:18.040 --> 00:19.679
Which do you consider
the more handsome?

00:19.680 --> 00:22.859
- Drum.
- Yes.

00:22.860 --> 00:24.279
Miss Reid.

00:24.280 --> 00:29.629
MAN: (SINGING) Little
girl, don't you lie to me.

00:29.630 --> 00:34.349
Tell me where did
you sleep last night.

00:34.350 --> 00:36.659
This is the only
peace he's known.

00:36.660 --> 00:39.270
I don't think Mr. Drake
would care for that very much.

