[FOOTSTEPS]

02:21.470 --> 02:22.970
[DOOR OPENING]

02:38.940 --> 02:40.430
[FOOTSTEPS]

02:47.920 --> 02:48.920
[SIGH]

02:53.910 --> 02:55.400
[FOOTSTEPS]

02:56.400 --> 02:57.400
[SCREAM]

03:09.880 --> 03:11.370
[NEIGHING]

03:14.370 --> 03:15.860
[METAL CREAKING]

03:22.350 --> 03:23.849
[SCREAM]

03:23.850 --> 03:26.340
[THEME MUSIC]

04:14.750 --> 04:17.488
MAN: Matilda, you'll be late.

04:17.490 --> 04:18.209
Mati-- wait.

04:18.211 --> 04:20.589
You sat here this whole night?

04:20.589 --> 04:22.979
What is this robs
you of your rest?

04:22.980 --> 04:23.970
Vampires?

04:23.971 --> 04:25.849
Really?
Go.

04:25.850 --> 04:26.850
Ready yourself.

04:32.430 --> 04:35.689
When the Count comes to
London, he makes his lair

04:35.690 --> 04:37.710
in Whitechapel like you.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.170
[DOOR OPENING]

04:43.650 --> 04:44.640
[CHILD CRYING]

04:44.641 --> 04:47.609
It's just a bad dream.

04:47.610 --> 04:49.489
What was that song, my love?

04:49.490 --> 04:51.219
WOMAN: Hm?

04:51.220 --> 04:52.729
The silly thing before.

04:52.730 --> 04:54.189
You know, the one
about the little girl.

04:54.190 --> 04:56.029
You were teaching me.

04:56.030 --> 04:57.479
[CLEARING THROAT]

04:57.480 --> 04:58.440
It's all right.

04:58.441 --> 05:00.369
It's all right.

05:00.370 --> 05:05.589
(SINGING) Little
girl, little girl.

05:05.590 --> 05:10.639
Don't lie to me.

05:10.640 --> 05:19.479
Tell me where did
you sleep last night.

05:19.480 --> 05:22.469
What sort of song
is that for a child?

05:22.470 --> 05:26.379
It works, though, doesn't it?

05:26.380 --> 05:28.880
[HUMMING]

05:35.870 --> 05:44.849
(SINGING) Tell me where
did you sleep last night?

05:44.850 --> 05:46.840
[MAN YELLING]

06:25.890 --> 06:26.890
Croker!

06:29.560 --> 06:31.089
[INAUDIBLE]?

06:31.090 --> 06:32.769
She's gone.

06:32.770 --> 06:34.169
What are you?
Simple?

06:34.170 --> 06:36.969
You didn't keep lookout,
you goddamn imbecile.

06:36.970 --> 06:40.019
Careful now, Captain.

06:40.020 --> 06:42.819
Nathaniel isn't fond
of such invective.

06:42.820 --> 06:46.859
Besides, your lady
is no rash girly.

06:46.860 --> 06:49.069
I doubt she [INAUDIBLE].

06:49.070 --> 06:51.859
She will not be far.

06:51.860 --> 06:55.479
You best hope he's right.

06:55.480 --> 06:57.450
[CHATTER]

07:11.250 --> 07:12.729
Jesus Christ, Caitlin.

07:12.730 --> 07:15.179
Have you lost your mind?

07:15.180 --> 07:16.549
I awoke.

07:16.550 --> 07:18.759
I reached for my son.

07:18.760 --> 07:20.370
And my son was not there.

07:23.680 --> 07:25.559
He is safe, and
he is cared for.

07:25.560 --> 07:26.799
And he will be yours again.

07:26.800 --> 07:28.419
Just time, darling.

07:28.420 --> 07:29.330
Come here.

07:29.331 --> 07:30.620
The burden of it is all.

07:35.930 --> 07:37.219
The sun is out, girl.

07:37.220 --> 07:40.339
And that face shines out
like a ruby in the rubble.

07:40.340 --> 07:41.559
I cannot shield
you if you will not

07:41.560 --> 07:43.409
confine yourself to quarters.

07:43.410 --> 07:44.779
Do not lecture me, Abel.

07:44.780 --> 07:47.059
I know the risk I take, and it
is a breath of dockside air,

07:47.060 --> 07:49.779
not tea at the Savoy.

07:49.780 --> 07:53.429
All fine and fair
and understood.

07:53.430 --> 07:54.659
Could you not snarl?

07:54.660 --> 07:56.299
We are fond of you.

07:56.300 --> 08:00.359
We prefer you safe
where we can see you.

08:00.360 --> 08:02.040
Not back on a gibbet
where we cannot.

08:05.160 --> 08:08.059
Now will you return
yourself to your bunk

08:08.060 --> 08:12.209
or will Nate here pull
you over his shoulder?

08:12.210 --> 08:13.270
You just let him try.

08:19.680 --> 08:21.799
Ah.
Come on.

08:21.800 --> 08:22.800
Business around.

08:30.990 --> 08:32.960
[CHATTER]
- Hurry.

08:36.419 --> 08:38.839
Oh, Inspector Drake,
Inspector Reid.

08:38.840 --> 08:40.078
It is the new cold store, sir.

08:40.080 --> 08:41.208
It's this way.

08:41.210 --> 08:45.309
They may keep meat for six
months before it spoils.

08:45.310 --> 08:47.239
Six months?

08:47.240 --> 08:48.920
Who wants mutton
that's half a year old?

09:01.630 --> 09:04.079
Number 25.

09:04.080 --> 09:05.519
Sirs, a word of caution.

09:05.520 --> 09:07.939
It ain't pretty.

09:07.940 --> 09:09.390
[DOOR OPENING]

09:14.240 --> 09:15.240
God's teeth.

09:36.450 --> 09:37.320
Jackson.

09:37.321 --> 09:40.259
Jackson.

09:40.260 --> 09:42.049
Oh, the American, sir?

09:42.050 --> 09:44.679
Yeah, I've banged
that drum, Mr. Drake.

09:44.680 --> 09:49.219
Ordered that, the, uh, carbon
lights be brought [INAUDIBLE].

09:49.220 --> 09:50.220
A man learns.

09:54.240 --> 09:56.000
The hanging man's
wrists are bound.

10:01.470 --> 10:05.109
There was someone else
restrained here, therefore.

10:05.110 --> 10:07.490
There's their spray--
a lot of it, too.

10:11.200 --> 10:12.519
Mr. Thatcher!

10:12.520 --> 10:15.009
Yeah?

10:15.010 --> 10:17.529
Whoever sat here was
either spirited away

10:17.530 --> 10:19.199
or left on their own engine.

10:19.200 --> 10:22.399
If the latter, having
lost this weight of blood,

10:22.400 --> 10:24.169
they will not have gone far.
[SIGH]

10:24.170 --> 10:25.979
I'll have the men pick
the market clean, sir.

10:25.980 --> 10:26.850
You do that, [INAUDIBLE].

10:26.850 --> 10:27.850
THATCHER: Yeah.

10:34.100 --> 10:35.540
[SIZZLING]

10:40.870 --> 10:45.449
Skin penetrated at the
jugular, at the radial

10:45.450 --> 10:47.159
beneath the bicep.

10:47.160 --> 10:47.930
This?

10:47.931 --> 10:49.459
It's another lancing.

10:49.460 --> 10:52.339
Older, however, less
precise instrument.

10:52.340 --> 10:53.349
And this is what killed him?

10:53.350 --> 10:54.350
The bloodletting?

10:54.351 --> 10:57.039
No, ligature marks.

10:57.040 --> 10:59.659
I bet he was strangled, killed.

10:59.660 --> 11:01.889
And only then is his blood let.

11:01.890 --> 11:04.169
To what end, however?

11:04.170 --> 11:07.089
The blood is the end.

11:07.090 --> 11:11.059
This poor bastard's
cadaver's been exsanguinated.

11:11.060 --> 11:13.959
Every last droplet
syphoned out of him.

11:13.960 --> 11:16.429
Why, do you suppose?

11:16.430 --> 11:21.629
The other party-- bound to
that chair-- she's found, sirs.

11:21.630 --> 11:23.990
Get more.
Get everything.

11:29.970 --> 11:32.379
Another puncture wound.

11:32.380 --> 11:34.079
Same message.

11:34.080 --> 11:35.830
But no ligature marks, however.

11:40.700 --> 11:44.419
She was alive while they
tried to syphon blood from her.

11:44.420 --> 11:46.049
- But escaped.
- She held her neck.

11:46.050 --> 11:47.899
She hoped to stanch
the blood flow

11:47.900 --> 11:49.109
even as she ran for her life.

11:53.970 --> 11:54.970
[SIGH]

11:59.220 --> 12:00.220
No defence wounds.

12:06.160 --> 12:07.630
[SIGH]

12:12.180 --> 12:13.359
[INAUDIBLE]

12:13.360 --> 12:17.069
Inner mucous membrane undamaged.

12:17.070 --> 12:20.840
No haemorrhaging
of the capillaries.

12:33.790 --> 12:34.780
Third and fourth.

12:34.781 --> 12:37.769
Oh, shit.

12:37.770 --> 12:39.239
What's that?

12:39.240 --> 12:39.990
What more?

12:39.991 --> 12:41.279
What do you think this is?

12:41.280 --> 12:44.179
A crystal ball?

12:44.180 --> 12:45.239
Did you find the other?

12:45.240 --> 12:47.499
Young woman,
puncture wound here.

12:47.500 --> 12:48.979
No strangulation, however.

12:48.980 --> 12:51.709
Oh, have Thatcher
bring 'em home.

12:51.710 --> 12:53.100
I need my knives.

12:56.360 --> 12:59.469
Where do you go?

12:59.470 --> 13:00.900
About my work, Drake.

13:11.440 --> 13:13.880
[YELLING]

13:16.810 --> 13:20.429
The hematoma about the
man's neck is from a rope.

13:20.430 --> 13:22.179
The insides of his
cheeks are unbitten.

13:22.180 --> 13:24.409
There are no burst
capillaries in his eyes.

13:24.410 --> 13:26.509
Therefore, he's not strangled.

13:26.510 --> 13:28.299
His neck is fractured clean
at the third and fourth

13:28.300 --> 13:30.899
cervical vertebrae, and
he's at least 120 pounds.

13:30.900 --> 13:34.089
Do you see where I'm
going yet, Doctor?

13:34.090 --> 13:36.059
Now such a break on
the neck of a man

13:36.060 --> 13:38.759
as such weight, that's
a drop of, uh-- why,

13:38.760 --> 13:41.599
seven feet, at least.

13:41.600 --> 13:44.349
Professional work.

13:44.350 --> 13:46.329
The kind of work that
puts me [INAUDIBLE]

13:46.330 --> 13:49.879
Standing over your
hangman's recent execution,

13:49.880 --> 13:51.559
pronouncing 'em dead.

13:51.560 --> 13:55.979
That's, uh, impressive
police work, Captain.

13:55.980 --> 13:58.239
Yet no policeman you.

13:58.240 --> 14:00.939
I wonder have you
shared your expert

14:00.940 --> 14:03.749
imaginings with your
friends on Leman Street?

14:03.750 --> 14:05.049
No?

14:05.050 --> 14:07.089
I wonder why that might be.

14:07.090 --> 14:12.969
If not because you fear what
I might choose to tell them.

14:12.970 --> 14:14.739
Do you not recall
my promise to you?

14:14.740 --> 14:18.239
Or is that you
doubt my sincerity?

14:18.240 --> 14:21.809
Now will you assist in
my inquiry or won't you?

14:21.810 --> 14:24.019
Which recently hanged
cadavers have you

14:24.020 --> 14:28.169
seen diverted from burial pits
no longer than two days passed?

14:28.170 --> 14:29.570
[SIGH]

14:30.980 --> 14:32.449
Two details.

14:32.450 --> 14:34.920
His name and where you sent him.

14:42.420 --> 14:45.039
Meet Percival Monks.

14:45.040 --> 14:47.979
He staved his mother-in-law's
head in with a fire iron.

14:47.980 --> 14:50.009
Got the rope for his troubles.

14:50.010 --> 14:52.769
Newgate hanged him yesterday,
sent his body to the London

14:52.770 --> 14:55.609
hospital for evisceration.

14:55.610 --> 14:58.269
How have you done
this, Jackson?

14:58.270 --> 15:01.050
Just merely read
the signs, Inspector.

15:04.730 --> 15:08.889
Now are we moving on, or do you
wish me to showboat further?

15:08.890 --> 15:09.800
Oh, no.

15:09.800 --> 15:10.800
Please, move on.

15:13.890 --> 15:14.890
[SIGH]

15:17.180 --> 15:20.189
Uh, [INAUDIBLE] tongue.

15:20.190 --> 15:23.829
Teeth as loose as the
keys in a saloon piano.

15:23.830 --> 15:25.709
Drake?

15:25.710 --> 15:26.789
Scurvy.

15:26.790 --> 15:29.070
Privation suffered on a
migrant's passage perhaps.

15:37.440 --> 15:38.230
Polish.

15:38.231 --> 15:39.929
Prayer card.

15:39.930 --> 15:42.509
It's Mark 3:11.

15:42.510 --> 15:43.552
Curious it isn't English.

15:46.090 --> 15:49.810
It said Mark what?
3:11.

15:53.690 --> 15:56.119
There we are.

15:56.120 --> 16:02.169
"And unclean spirits, when they
saw him, fell down before him."

16:02.170 --> 16:04.789
There's more here, however.

16:04.790 --> 16:05.510
You see here?

16:05.511 --> 16:08.429
This is indigo staining in here.

16:08.430 --> 16:11.269
That's the mild scarring
of seamstress needles.

16:11.270 --> 16:12.569
She's been [INAUDIBLE].

16:12.570 --> 16:13.709
That'd be my assumption.

16:13.710 --> 16:15.639
Polish Catholics are only
recently so visible in the city

16:15.640 --> 16:16.340
there.

16:16.341 --> 16:17.719
And the numbers
are not so swollen

16:17.720 --> 16:20.939
that finding one such from
a Whitechapel sweatshop

16:20.940 --> 16:22.759
should be beyond us.

16:22.760 --> 16:25.479
What do you say what made
an end of her, Jackson?

16:25.480 --> 16:27.329
I'm at a loss, Drake.

16:27.330 --> 16:29.599
Genuinely.

16:29.600 --> 16:31.419
It's not the bloodletting
that done for her, then?

16:31.420 --> 16:32.330
No, not at all.

16:32.331 --> 16:36.599
Point in fact, she
ain't been bled at all.

16:36.600 --> 16:38.519
Can you account for the
blood that covered her?

16:38.520 --> 16:40.079
I cannot.

16:40.080 --> 16:43.379
The sole wound on her is
the exact same puncturing

16:43.380 --> 16:44.949
of the neck with
the same instrument,

16:44.950 --> 16:46.389
but it's not been
used to drain her.

16:46.390 --> 16:51.869
On the contrary, she's,
uh-- well, complete.

16:51.870 --> 16:56.179
As we discussed, perhaps, it
is not the end that is germain--

16:56.180 --> 16:57.419
not the end, but the means.

16:57.420 --> 16:59.689
This is a clean
wound, is it not?

16:59.690 --> 17:01.219
There's nothing savage.

17:01.220 --> 17:03.069
It is precise.

17:03.070 --> 17:04.348
One might even say skilled.

17:04.349 --> 17:06.059
And whether it is
drained or not,

17:06.060 --> 17:10.169
it is the blood that is
a chief interest here.

17:10.170 --> 17:11.420
Why preserve a dead thing?

17:16.329 --> 17:18.419
What is it that happens to
blood when it decays, Captain?

17:18.420 --> 17:19.719
It clots, does it not?

17:19.720 --> 17:23.789
Unless you keep it cold, Reid.

17:23.790 --> 17:25.699
Puncture wounds
administered with skill

17:25.700 --> 17:28.079
and with clean
instruments-- an act

17:28.079 --> 17:30.769
carried out in the full
knowledge of a clinical need

17:30.770 --> 17:31.829
for refrigeration.

17:31.830 --> 17:33.720
Such as the cold store
at the meat market.

17:37.860 --> 17:40.589
This man-- this
executed cadaver--

17:40.590 --> 17:43.839
a recent property, we are
told, of the London hospital.

17:43.840 --> 17:45.819
It is a medical stripe
of man we search for.

17:45.820 --> 17:46.899
Mr. Reid.

17:46.900 --> 17:48.739
I do not forget what the
place once meant here.

17:48.740 --> 17:50.669
Well, would you take
a turn around to London

17:50.670 --> 17:51.370
this afternoon?

17:51.371 --> 17:52.949
See how it is they
misplaced this corpse.

17:52.950 --> 17:54.169
I shall, Inspector.

17:54.170 --> 17:57.119
And I shall pay a visit
to our Polish community.

17:57.120 --> 17:58.120
Sergeant Thatcher.

18:00.250 --> 18:00.950
Yes.

18:00.951 --> 18:05.089
You and I are out to
kick some rocks over.

18:05.090 --> 18:07.849
You.

18:07.850 --> 18:09.340
You find what killed her.

18:17.420 --> 18:19.319
I cannot fathom while it's
allowed to continue unabated,

18:19.320 --> 18:21.369
sir.
It's [INAUDIBLE].

18:21.370 --> 18:23.079
We need to close the city gates.

18:23.080 --> 18:25.229
Can they not take their
suffering elsewhere?

18:25.230 --> 18:27.679
We've got plenty
enough of our own.

18:27.680 --> 18:30.529
All compassion, are
you not, Sergeant?

18:30.530 --> 18:31.320
Well--

18:31.321 --> 18:33.889
Just kick the door down then.

18:33.890 --> 18:35.309
[CHATTER]

18:35.310 --> 18:36.310
[THUD]

18:38.150 --> 18:40.049
[WHISPERING]

18:40.050 --> 18:42.119
She's a Polish
woman-- 20 years old.

18:42.120 --> 18:45.229
Most likely absent
only since last night.

18:45.230 --> 18:46.230
[WHISPERING]

18:48.700 --> 18:52.710
Now have a look at
her photograph here.

18:56.190 --> 18:57.359
She is dead.

18:57.360 --> 18:59.129
See?

18:59.130 --> 19:01.199
Murdered not half
a mile from here.

19:01.200 --> 19:04.329
Does she not have one friend
who would speak for her?

19:04.330 --> 19:05.160
[COUGHING]

19:05.161 --> 19:06.669
Will you not look, miss?

19:06.670 --> 19:08.150
[SPEAKING POLISH]

19:12.880 --> 19:13.670
I'm sorry, miss.

19:13.671 --> 19:14.770
I don't speak Polish.

19:27.220 --> 19:28.710
[COUGHING]

19:32.230 --> 19:33.479
Why will you not look, miss?

19:33.480 --> 19:34.270
WOMAN: Please, sir.

19:34.271 --> 19:35.779
You need to talk
with the foreman.

19:35.780 --> 19:39.019
Pardon me, miss.

19:39.020 --> 19:41.239
This wound needs attention.

19:41.240 --> 19:42.719
Will you let us see to it?

19:42.720 --> 19:43.620
No.

19:43.621 --> 19:45.779
I have made no
request for your help.

19:45.780 --> 19:48.650
Now, please, the foreman
will return, and I must work.

19:52.630 --> 19:53.620
[SIGH]

19:53.621 --> 19:55.549
To hell with your
wretched foreman, miss.

19:55.550 --> 19:56.280
You're coming with us.

19:56.281 --> 19:57.719
[SPEAKING POLISH]
- Come on!

19:57.720 --> 19:58.610
Calm down.

19:58.611 --> 20:00.320
[SPEAKING POLISH]

20:07.930 --> 20:08.930
Agnieszka.

20:11.470 --> 20:12.470
This was her name.

20:15.290 --> 20:16.290
A friend?

20:20.140 --> 20:21.140
Our mothers were.

20:23.630 --> 20:25.419
She was given an address
where to find me.

20:25.420 --> 20:31.589
I-- I helped her find work.

20:31.590 --> 20:33.799
Captain Jackson, the young
lady has an infected wound.

20:33.800 --> 20:34.500
Would you mind--

20:34.501 --> 20:35.969
You see a starched cap
atop my head, Drake?

20:35.970 --> 20:39.249
A high white collar
about my neck?

20:39.250 --> 20:40.140
I do not.

20:40.141 --> 20:43.459
Well, then I cannot imagine
why you mistook me for a nurse.

20:43.460 --> 20:45.079
Bandages and iodine.

20:45.080 --> 20:46.200
You know how to use them.

20:51.380 --> 20:54.369
Here, let me.

20:54.370 --> 20:55.650
Basic training, you know, sir.

21:13.740 --> 21:14.720
Pardon me, miss.

21:14.721 --> 21:17.439
And she left not word
of where she was going?

21:17.440 --> 21:19.949
She just vanished, you say?

21:19.950 --> 21:24.279
If she had left word, it would
not have been a vanishing,

21:24.280 --> 21:25.280
would it?

21:29.620 --> 21:32.169
Now, please, I must leave.

21:32.170 --> 21:33.889
Or there will be no
work when I return.

21:33.890 --> 21:38.129
I will starve, and that will be
on your conscience, Inspector.

21:38.130 --> 21:39.439
Uh-uh-uh, no, miss.

21:39.440 --> 21:43.039
You will not talk
to me of conscience.

21:43.040 --> 21:45.929
That girl down there
looked to you for leading.

21:45.930 --> 21:49.769
Seems to me you led her
nowhere but her death.

21:49.770 --> 21:54.729
Now you wish to leave
us, you will speak to me.

21:54.730 --> 21:57.039
Or I will arrest you, miss.

21:57.040 --> 21:58.770
Put you in a cell
and forget for why.

22:03.370 --> 22:07.689
She said only that she had
been asked to meet a man.

22:07.690 --> 22:11.469
A man who said that she
had only to come with him,

22:11.470 --> 22:13.679
and she would be paid 1,000
times over what she would

22:13.680 --> 22:15.029
make with a needle in her hand.

22:15.030 --> 22:18.419
She was to sell herself.

22:18.420 --> 22:21.599
Spread her legs
for money, you mean?

22:21.600 --> 22:24.179
No, I did-- I-- I just--

22:24.180 --> 22:26.810
But that was not it.
She swore to me.

22:34.750 --> 22:35.740
[SIGH]

22:35.741 --> 22:38.219
It must be that she was robbed.

22:38.220 --> 22:40.659
- Killed for the money she earned.
- No, miss.

22:40.660 --> 22:43.229
It wasn't a robbing of
her that caused her death.

22:43.230 --> 22:45.490
It was a good deal too much
trouble taken for that.

22:48.770 --> 22:55.039
Then if you, a policeman, do
not know, I cannot see how I,

22:55.040 --> 22:57.319
a seamstress, can help you.

22:57.320 --> 22:59.599
Now may I return
to see if I have

22:59.600 --> 23:02.249
been discharged from my work?

23:02.250 --> 23:05.540
- See her returned.
- Yes, Inspector.

23:15.900 --> 23:17.209
[CHATTER]
- Don't you miss it then?

23:17.210 --> 23:18.130
Your home?

23:18.130 --> 23:19.060
[INAUDIBLE]?

23:19.061 --> 23:20.449
Ah.

23:20.450 --> 23:21.450
I chose to leave.

23:25.220 --> 23:27.769
It came to not
feel like my home.

23:27.770 --> 23:32.829
Home is a kind place, and
there was too much unkindness.

23:32.830 --> 23:34.269
So you're happy
never to return?

23:34.270 --> 23:36.749
I did not say that.

23:36.750 --> 23:38.879
You-- you are from here?

23:38.880 --> 23:41.239
Near enough, yeah.

23:41.240 --> 23:43.299
But only today you
see the street signs

23:43.300 --> 23:46.009
and the sound the [INAUDIBLE].

23:46.010 --> 23:49.399
You know you leave
where you're from,

23:49.400 --> 23:53.289
and a reminder therefore
of who you are.

23:53.290 --> 23:57.019
I suppose so, yeah.

23:57.020 --> 23:58.020
Those things I miss.

24:02.560 --> 24:03.560
That him?

24:13.090 --> 24:16.339
She knows trouble from you,
sir, and you will know worse.

24:16.340 --> 24:17.340
Huh?

24:32.330 --> 24:34.339
The sight of blood
frighten you, Drummond?

24:34.340 --> 24:37.789
Not in small amounts, Captain.

24:37.790 --> 24:41.150
Well, it frightens
some, however.

24:44.010 --> 24:50.949
It's an instinctive phobia, as
inescapable a part of any man

24:50.950 --> 24:57.219
as, well, his blood itself.

24:57.220 --> 24:59.010
You know where
Wyoming is, Drummond?

25:02.190 --> 25:03.639
It's in America, I imagine.

25:03.640 --> 25:06.549
Take a prize.

25:06.550 --> 25:11.669
There's big mountains there
and big, high mountain

25:11.670 --> 25:15.419
passes full of virgin snow.

25:15.420 --> 25:19.119
Now I saw a man--
a friend of mine,

25:19.120 --> 25:24.029
as it goes-- Comanche
brave put a hunting

25:24.030 --> 25:26.239
knife through his guts before
I could get a shot off.

25:28.720 --> 25:31.709
My friend died.

25:31.710 --> 25:33.769
And I'm a doctor, understand?

25:33.770 --> 25:43.419
So-- well, the--
the impotence of it.

25:43.420 --> 25:49.329
All I could do was watch as
blood spread through the eyes.

25:49.330 --> 25:53.230
A white world made red.

25:59.070 --> 26:00.070
[KNOCKING]

26:01.020 --> 26:02.649
Miss Mathilda.

26:02.650 --> 26:04.909
Your visits are a
ray of sunshine.

26:04.910 --> 26:06.439
Here, come, sit.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.369
Join me.

26:08.370 --> 26:10.029
I am eager to know
what latest there

26:10.030 --> 26:11.749
is concerning Samuel Drummond.

26:11.750 --> 26:13.399
Have you now spoken with him?

26:13.400 --> 26:16.729
I have, but he is,
I believe, bashful.

26:16.730 --> 26:17.500
[LAUGHS]

26:17.501 --> 26:19.579
And timidity, so
the world insists,

26:19.580 --> 26:22.219
is the preserver of our sex.

26:22.220 --> 26:24.729
You seek to draw him out then?

26:24.730 --> 26:29.259
I seek to know him a little--
what might make him sad

26:29.260 --> 26:31.799
or happy or excited or afraid.

26:31.800 --> 26:35.269
There are means by which you
might discover such, Mathilda.

26:35.270 --> 26:37.189
It is no magic.

26:37.190 --> 26:40.849
Merely offer him the opportunity
to know something of yours.

26:40.850 --> 26:43.539
Show him something about which
you might earn a passion.

26:43.540 --> 26:46.639
See if then he might share
his thoughts on it with you.

26:46.640 --> 26:47.819
That is wise counsel.

26:47.820 --> 26:48.820
Thank you.

26:52.840 --> 26:55.550
There is no one else with whom
I might share such questions.

27:00.710 --> 27:02.630
- Not your father?
- No.

27:08.330 --> 27:10.179
Do you travel somewhere,
Miss Castello?

27:10.180 --> 27:11.739
Paris.

27:11.740 --> 27:16.209
It is no gentle tour,
however, but work of the sort.

27:16.210 --> 27:19.889
The story hunted down.

27:19.890 --> 27:22.069
Is it related to that
photograph you take with you?

27:22.070 --> 27:25.329
Of the man who was
my father's friend?

27:25.330 --> 27:27.029
Who that?

27:27.030 --> 27:30.339
Mr. Isaac Bloom and
the man, the rabbi,

27:30.340 --> 27:32.739
Ritofsky, who all thought
was killed by Isaac Bloom.

27:32.740 --> 27:35.659
He lived in Paris, did he not?

27:35.660 --> 27:39.809
And how would you know
such things, Mathilda Reid?

27:39.810 --> 27:40.810
[SIGH]

27:41.670 --> 27:45.149
My father keeps some
of his work at home.

27:45.150 --> 27:48.829
On occasion, I'm
interested to read it.

27:48.830 --> 27:53.479
Mathilda, there are few
women who will tell you this.

27:53.480 --> 27:56.769
But one of the greatest
qualities we might own

27:56.770 --> 27:59.749
is that of disobedience.

27:59.750 --> 28:00.750
[LAUGHS]

28:04.710 --> 28:05.700
[CHATTER]

28:05.700 --> 28:06.700
[NEIGHING]

28:08.180 --> 28:09.180
[COUGHING]

28:14.130 --> 28:16.889
TREVES: The moniker
Elephant Man was,

28:16.890 --> 28:21.689
of course, a showman's
adjectival indulgence.

28:21.690 --> 28:25.609
Joseph looked no more like
an elephant than I do.

28:25.610 --> 28:26.610
[LAUGHTER]

28:29.040 --> 28:33.579
We are keen as a
race to throw back,

28:33.580 --> 28:37.649
to attribute animal,
primal qualities to that

28:37.650 --> 28:39.319
which we do not understand.

28:39.320 --> 28:44.369
Here, deformity.

28:44.370 --> 28:49.379
Elsewhere, perhaps, foreigners.

28:49.380 --> 28:52.359
We can describe such
conditions to ourselves only

28:52.360 --> 28:55.899
in terms that are animalistic.

28:55.900 --> 28:59.319
Important then to think
not on what separated

28:59.320 --> 29:03.869
Mr. Merrick from
we, his brother-men,

29:03.870 --> 29:06.540
but rather what
joined him to us.

29:09.750 --> 29:11.149
Thank you.

29:11.150 --> 29:13.090
[CHATTER]

29:25.730 --> 29:27.219
Mr. Red.

29:27.220 --> 29:28.220
[DOOR CLOSING]

29:29.010 --> 29:32.719
Mr. Treves, hello.

29:32.720 --> 29:34.859
Inspector no more,
as I heard it?

29:34.860 --> 29:36.299
Inspector yet
again, I'm afraid.

29:36.300 --> 29:37.979
Afraid, sir?

29:37.980 --> 29:40.000
- Turn of phrase.
- Hm.

29:43.210 --> 29:45.879
He was consenting of
these, Mr. Merrick?

29:45.880 --> 29:46.880
He was.

29:51.990 --> 29:54.379
His abnormalities
sketched to aid

29:54.380 --> 29:56.699
the study of our similarities.

29:56.700 --> 29:58.659
Mr. Reid, forgive me.

29:58.660 --> 30:00.929
Do you come seven years
since your last visit

30:00.930 --> 30:02.959
to question my science?

30:02.960 --> 30:06.439
I do not, Mr. Treves.

30:06.440 --> 30:08.169
But the dissections
carried out here--

30:08.170 --> 30:10.339
there are indeed
certain questions

30:10.340 --> 30:13.249
that I seek answers for.

30:13.250 --> 30:15.819
The cadavers that are
sent to you from Newgate.

30:15.820 --> 30:17.469
A valuable resource, certainly.

30:17.470 --> 30:19.649
You have records from them?

30:19.650 --> 30:20.650
Of course.

30:25.130 --> 30:27.279
My thanks.

30:27.280 --> 30:29.079
Yesterday, you say?

30:29.080 --> 30:33.069
Yes, the name
Monks, as I heard it.

30:33.070 --> 30:35.100
No.
As you see, no such name.

30:41.110 --> 30:42.519
No, indeed.

30:42.520 --> 30:44.269
A wasted visit then.

30:44.270 --> 30:46.279
Oh, never that, Mr. Reid.

30:46.280 --> 30:47.559
Mr. Treves, tell me.

30:47.560 --> 30:51.299
The cadaver's whose origin I
seek-- we have him currently.

30:51.300 --> 30:54.889
He was found perhaps one day
after his Newgate execution.

30:54.890 --> 30:57.099
His neck punctured.

30:57.100 --> 30:59.029
His body inverted.

30:59.030 --> 31:00.280
And it entirely exsanguinated.

31:04.270 --> 31:07.319
Now were it a means
rather than an ends?

31:07.320 --> 31:08.459
I know it is not orthodox.

31:08.460 --> 31:09.639
See, I understand that.

31:09.640 --> 31:12.719
But-- but the fringes of
medical practise, to take

31:12.720 --> 31:14.109
blood and then preserve it.

31:14.110 --> 31:18.189
What purpose can you
imagine for such an action?

31:18.190 --> 31:20.399
Knowledge.

31:20.400 --> 31:23.169
To know.

31:23.170 --> 31:24.080
Blood is life.

31:24.081 --> 31:30.530
How might that life be
taken, preserved, handed on?

31:34.790 --> 31:35.790
Mr. Treves.

31:42.370 --> 31:45.569
I always recommend a smoke
when you're two pints down.

31:45.570 --> 31:48.529
Never known a head rush like it.

31:48.530 --> 31:51.039
Ah, Inspectors.

31:51.040 --> 31:55.659
You've come for some answers,
and now I have a few.

31:55.660 --> 31:57.749
Your, uh-- your lady there--

31:57.750 --> 31:59.509
Her name was Agnieszka.

31:59.510 --> 32:00.430
Ah.

32:00.431 --> 32:02.489
Well, now I know her name.

32:02.490 --> 32:05.099
And what killed her.

32:05.100 --> 32:06.429
And so?

32:06.430 --> 32:08.629
It was organ collapse.

32:08.630 --> 32:13.489
Almost total internal collapse--
heart, kidneys, bladder, liver.

32:13.490 --> 32:20.339
And the cause of that failure
was a corruption in her blood.

32:20.340 --> 32:22.189
Come see.

32:22.190 --> 32:24.299
Now you know where the
haemoglobin is, Reid,

32:24.300 --> 32:25.200
I assume that?

32:25.201 --> 32:27.799
It is a compound which carries
oxygen through the blood

32:27.800 --> 32:28.580
to the organs.

32:28.581 --> 32:29.989
Ever eager student, this one.

32:29.990 --> 32:31.782
Now this is Agnieszka's blood.
Take a look.

32:42.770 --> 32:44.969
Her blood ain't carrying
nothing no where.

32:44.970 --> 32:46.299
That's the organ failure?

32:46.300 --> 32:49.289
Now--

32:49.290 --> 32:51.409
Have you bled the
whole division?

32:51.410 --> 32:52.889
Save you two, almost.

32:52.890 --> 32:54.670
Now I take two
different samples.

33:05.430 --> 33:06.630
Reid, make a comparison.

33:11.820 --> 33:12.959
It is clotting.

33:12.960 --> 33:18.249
The men's blood
meet and corrupt.

33:18.250 --> 33:21.549
We say then that the blood
that covered her as she

33:21.550 --> 33:23.289
ran-- it was not hers.

33:23.290 --> 33:26.799
But his-- piped from him
into her through the puncture

33:26.800 --> 33:27.500
in her neck.

33:27.501 --> 33:30.899
Only she feels her body rebel,
the panic of it, and runs.

33:30.900 --> 33:32.409
But why?

33:32.410 --> 33:33.479
Why do this?

33:33.480 --> 33:36.419
The care taken-- it cannot be
for cruelty, for death alone.

33:36.420 --> 33:39.489
Even a vampire inflicts
death so that he may live.

33:39.490 --> 33:43.219
But what if two men's blood
does not always corrupt?

33:43.220 --> 33:45.219
Now what if my blood
is somehow different

33:45.220 --> 33:47.869
from yours but akin to Drake's?

33:47.870 --> 33:49.089
As if I don't have
troubles enough.

33:49.090 --> 33:50.609
Thatcher here, for example.

33:50.610 --> 33:55.249
Now I mixed his blood with, uh,
your hanging man there, Monk's.

33:55.250 --> 33:56.250
Take a look.

34:00.430 --> 34:01.430
It prospers.

34:06.110 --> 34:07.609
Thatcher.

34:07.610 --> 34:12.248
Thatcher, you-- you
are a match for him.

34:12.250 --> 34:15.289
So together they make life.

34:15.290 --> 34:19.958
This earlier lancing you
identified, Captain--

34:19.960 --> 34:21.599
The puncture wound infected.

34:21.600 --> 34:23.139
Could this be
the means by which

34:23.139 --> 34:24.609
a-- a sampling took place?

34:24.610 --> 34:28.309
And the pre-selecting of
a correlating blood match.

34:28.310 --> 34:31.668
Inspector Drake, the, uh-- the
wound [INAUDIBLE] on the girl

34:31.670 --> 34:34.739
is the same infection, do we--
do we say perhaps that meant

34:34.739 --> 34:35.739
[INAUDIBLE] was a match?

34:39.190 --> 34:46.580
And not Agnieszka who has
no such infected wounds.

34:50.100 --> 34:51.918
Did she go in Magdalena's
stead therefore?

34:51.920 --> 34:53.649
Her blood, no match.

34:53.650 --> 34:56.480
It corrupted, and her
death brought down.

34:59.300 --> 35:02.379
And this man, Monks,
here-- his sampling

35:02.380 --> 35:04.739
could only have happened before
his execution for the blood

35:04.740 --> 35:05.740
to be alive.

35:13.630 --> 35:16.919
Mr. Drummond, run
a records search.

35:16.920 --> 35:19.559
Magdalena Dobrowski, 23.

35:19.560 --> 35:21.169
I expect you'll find
she spent some time

35:21.170 --> 35:24.389
behind the walls of Newgate.

35:24.390 --> 35:27.449
It is curious, this, Captain.

35:27.450 --> 35:31.109
But Mr. Treves's records show
no transfer of this man's

35:31.110 --> 35:32.810
cadaver from Newgate to London.

35:36.510 --> 35:40.379
Do we must assume your
source corrupted, also?

35:40.380 --> 35:41.870
[RINGING]

35:43.420 --> 35:44.420
Drummond!

35:46.920 --> 35:47.989
Yes.

35:47.990 --> 35:48.730
Thank you.

35:48.731 --> 35:51.749
Four months for
the theft of bread.

35:51.750 --> 35:52.560
You find that girl.

35:52.561 --> 35:53.599
You bring her back.

35:53.600 --> 35:55.809
I imagine we are to
Newgate, Inspector.

35:55.810 --> 35:57.289
Quite so, Mr. Reid.

35:57.290 --> 36:00.429
Oh, Jackson, best you come, too.

36:00.430 --> 36:02.230
Introduce us to that
source of yours.

36:11.410 --> 36:14.429
You lied to me, Probyn.

36:14.430 --> 36:18.319
Who did you pass Percival
Monks' cadaver to, sir?

36:18.320 --> 36:20.769
Uh, the disposal
of prison remains

36:20.770 --> 36:24.059
is very far from my
responsibility, Inspector.

36:24.060 --> 36:26.459
The London hospital
is where such cadavers

36:26.460 --> 36:28.969
are, under normal
circumstances, sent.

36:28.970 --> 36:31.359
If one has gone astray,
then it has not done

36:31.360 --> 36:32.669
so from within my agreement.

36:32.670 --> 36:34.420
Where is it you keep
your needles, Doctor?

36:37.630 --> 36:39.050
You have the key about you?

37:03.680 --> 37:06.659
Instrument's much used, sir.

37:06.660 --> 37:07.969
Blunted, in fact.

37:07.970 --> 37:11.669
I am provided with but a
modest stipend, Mr. Reid.

37:11.670 --> 37:14.119
I'm sure.

37:14.120 --> 37:17.779
Mr. Monks had a needle
fester wound on his arm,

37:17.780 --> 37:19.289
here, in the crook of his elbow.

37:19.290 --> 37:22.320
A Polish woman, Magdalena
Dobrowski, likewise, Doctor.

37:26.600 --> 37:27.839
To what end such
needling, Doctor?

37:27.840 --> 37:32.779
I, uh-- in-- in an enclosed
environment such as this,

37:32.780 --> 37:35.679
outbreaks of disease
are all too common.

37:35.680 --> 37:38.969
My-- my duty would be
neglected if I did not attempt

37:38.970 --> 37:41.650
to contain them by inoculation.

37:45.160 --> 37:46.559
And this?

37:46.560 --> 37:49.349
If you please.

37:49.350 --> 37:50.809
No, sir.

37:50.810 --> 37:53.829
No, I-- I will not
be so suspected.

37:53.830 --> 37:54.999
I am a doctor.

37:55.000 --> 37:58.879
My entire life given to the
care of-- of these incarcerate

37:58.880 --> 37:59.780
wrecks and villains.

37:59.781 --> 38:02.719
I-- I will have some
respect, dammit!

38:02.720 --> 38:04.070
[GLASS BREAKING]

38:05.220 --> 38:06.220
Oops.

38:17.070 --> 38:19.280
Magdalena.
Magdalena.

38:23.100 --> 38:24.100
[SPEAKING POLISH]

38:25.340 --> 38:26.130
Magdalena!

38:26.130 --> 38:26.920
Where is she?

38:26.920 --> 38:27.920
Where is she?

38:30.350 --> 38:31.350
[WHISPERING]

38:33.880 --> 38:36.809
As I heard it, Frank, you were
asked to return in company,

38:36.810 --> 38:38.009
not alone.

38:38.010 --> 38:38.710
Drum.

38:38.711 --> 38:40.939
Do you wish me to take that
reading machine of yours

38:40.940 --> 38:42.219
and bury it in your head?

38:42.220 --> 38:43.889
Not overly, Sergeant.

38:43.890 --> 38:47.070
Then stop being a lobcock and
tell me where they put Probyn.

39:13.800 --> 39:15.289
Hello?

39:15.290 --> 39:17.830
Please, I have come as asked.

39:27.210 --> 39:28.769
That is understood.

39:28.770 --> 39:29.550
Thank you, Governor.

39:29.550 --> 39:30.540
Of course.

39:30.541 --> 39:31.989
His alibi is sound?

39:31.990 --> 39:33.409
It is.

39:33.410 --> 39:36.119
When Agnieszka was
killed, Dr. Carlyle Probyn

39:36.120 --> 39:38.749
was enjoying supper with the
Newgate board of trustees.

39:38.750 --> 39:40.139
In any event, I
did not have him

39:40.140 --> 39:41.959
pinned for this type of work.

39:41.960 --> 39:45.159
One way or another, he is
part of this chain, however.

39:45.160 --> 39:47.699
Sirs, you must come.

39:47.700 --> 39:48.700
[YELLING]

39:53.320 --> 39:54.369
Where?

39:54.370 --> 39:57.059
You tell me where she is.

39:57.060 --> 39:57.990
[GRUNT]

39:57.991 --> 40:00.789
Huh?

40:00.790 --> 40:01.899
Explain yourself, son!

40:01.900 --> 40:03.149
She's gone, sir.

40:03.150 --> 40:04.770
- Who has?
- Magdalena is gone.

40:08.040 --> 40:09.040
Get out!

40:14.200 --> 40:15.929
Captain Jackson to attend
an injury in the cells

40:15.930 --> 40:16.930
immediately.

40:19.780 --> 40:22.129
PROBYN: Who do you think I am?

40:22.130 --> 40:24.719
Some drunken [INAUDIBLE]?

40:24.720 --> 40:25.720
I am not.

40:28.840 --> 40:31.499
I'll have your warrant
cards for this.

40:31.500 --> 40:34.059
What if I took blood
from our inmates?

40:34.060 --> 40:37.199
Is there a law
that says I cannot?

40:37.200 --> 40:39.099
No.

40:39.100 --> 40:41.649
- I am a public servant.
- No, sir.

40:41.650 --> 40:44.650
You are an accessory to murder.

40:51.140 --> 40:54.420
You have no option but to
release me, and you know it.

40:59.760 --> 41:02.219
Well, let me, uh, patch you
up at least before you go, huh?

41:08.170 --> 41:09.650
[PANTING]

41:19.510 --> 41:20.990
[GROAN]

41:21.970 --> 41:22.960
[GASP]

41:22.961 --> 41:23.979
No.

41:23.980 --> 41:27.889
Uh, they do not improve
your health, I believe.

41:27.890 --> 41:29.889
Shit, Probyn.

41:29.890 --> 41:32.779
What does?

41:32.780 --> 41:33.780
[GROAN]

41:35.200 --> 41:37.149
Ah, it's superficial.

41:37.150 --> 41:38.609
You'll live.

41:38.610 --> 41:39.570
[SIGH]

41:39.571 --> 41:41.030
[GROAN]

41:51.700 --> 41:54.169
No.

41:54.170 --> 41:56.130
You do her the honour
of looking at her.

42:14.950 --> 42:17.109
I thought you were
a doctor, Probyn.

42:17.110 --> 42:19.269
Such sights were humdrum.

42:19.270 --> 42:20.270
[WINCING]

42:21.950 --> 42:23.919
Then why the
discomfort unless you,

42:23.920 --> 42:29.239
uh-- if you feel some
responsibility for her.

42:29.240 --> 42:31.479
I have never once met her.

42:31.480 --> 42:32.480
Now what I'm saying.

42:36.020 --> 42:37.020
Now, come close.

42:39.900 --> 42:42.269
This is where he
ran the tubing in.

42:42.270 --> 42:45.769
Now your Magdalena--
the one whose blood

42:45.770 --> 42:49.339
you took while she served her
Newgate time-- all of this

42:49.340 --> 42:51.109
was meant for her.

42:51.110 --> 42:54.010
And it would have been
you that sent her there.

42:56.860 --> 43:06.549
Her sample-- and that
of the murderer Monk

43:06.550 --> 43:12.940
here also-- you matched them.

43:20.730 --> 43:23.389
[SCREAM]

43:23.390 --> 43:25.399
It's the rubbing alcohol.
My mistake.

43:25.400 --> 43:27.809
Still, there are worst mistakes
to stuff, wouldn't you say?

43:27.810 --> 43:29.449
By way of example, a
transfusion experiment

43:29.450 --> 43:30.609
on a girl with the wrong blood?

43:30.610 --> 43:32.439
[SCREAM]
Now!

43:32.440 --> 43:36.499
You matched Magdalena and Monks.

43:36.500 --> 43:37.400
I did.

43:37.401 --> 43:39.589
At whose instruction?

43:39.590 --> 43:41.379
A name.

43:41.380 --> 43:43.299
He was French, I believe.

43:43.300 --> 43:45.219
He did not give it.

43:45.220 --> 43:47.889
Well, what did he give you?

43:47.890 --> 43:49.960
Money.
A promise of more.

43:54.420 --> 43:58.059
Now we know how motivated you
are by that currency, don't we?

43:58.060 --> 44:00.699
It was for the
saving of a child.

44:00.700 --> 44:02.809
His child.

44:02.810 --> 44:04.749
And he was a doctor, correct?

44:04.750 --> 44:05.849
I mean, he would
have had to been

44:05.850 --> 44:07.619
to attempt such a thing with
a need to employ another

44:07.620 --> 44:08.639
such as yourself, Probyn.

44:08.640 --> 44:12.699
Did he-- did he say he'd
been struck off, or--

44:12.700 --> 44:14.199
Uh, no.

44:14.200 --> 44:16.730
Uh, but I-- I imagine it so.

44:20.920 --> 44:22.819
You know, Probyn.

44:22.820 --> 44:25.459
I think me and you may yet
escape this particular pickle

44:25.460 --> 44:26.460
in one piece.

44:29.730 --> 44:33.079
I never had a
daughter, you know.

44:33.080 --> 44:35.459
I should have
liked one, however.

44:35.460 --> 44:38.759
What benefit do you imagine
she might have carried?

44:38.760 --> 44:40.609
Well.

44:40.610 --> 44:42.930
No ship's head was ever made
from the figure of a man.

44:46.240 --> 44:47.730
[LAUGHTER]

44:49.210 --> 44:53.339
She would have been pleasing
to have about the place is all.

44:53.340 --> 44:55.779
Kind words, a pot of coffee.

44:55.780 --> 44:57.549
Sons do not offer such?

44:57.550 --> 44:59.029
They do not.

44:59.030 --> 45:00.580
They're altogether
a more bother.

45:04.280 --> 45:05.690
- Huh.
- The man, Nathaniel.

45:08.260 --> 45:08.960
He's yours?

45:08.961 --> 45:11.770
My responsibility, I
feel, if not my blood.

45:14.980 --> 45:16.449
You?

45:16.450 --> 45:17.450
You have a child?

45:21.050 --> 45:22.799
I do not believe you
would allow me to rest

45:22.800 --> 45:25.059
here ignorant of who I am.

45:25.060 --> 45:26.389
[LAUGHS]

45:26.390 --> 45:29.129
Or my monstrous crimes.

45:29.130 --> 45:30.390
Certainly that is true.

45:35.130 --> 45:37.969
They do not trouble you?

45:37.970 --> 45:40.170
The crimes?
Should they?

45:44.320 --> 45:51.339
There is-- one blacker.

45:51.340 --> 45:55.320
It felt blacker, I
mean, in my heart.

45:58.270 --> 46:01.069
Oh, believe me, child.

46:01.070 --> 46:03.730
Many is a fellow to have
lost his life on my account.

46:10.380 --> 46:13.919
You'll be calm in this school.

46:13.920 --> 46:18.919
Mine is not a place of
judgment or justice.

46:18.920 --> 46:21.690
I leave some refined
notions to others.

46:26.670 --> 46:28.749
Scotland Yard, British
Medical Association, the French

46:28.750 --> 46:30.259
Confederation, [INAUDIBLE].

46:30.260 --> 46:34.879
All that have been barred in
the last three years, say.

46:34.880 --> 46:36.599
Suggestion for the
cause of such barring

46:36.600 --> 46:37.699
is illegal
transfusion of bloods.

46:37.700 --> 46:39.369
Yes, Mr. Reid.

46:39.370 --> 46:41.129
Do no harm.

46:41.130 --> 46:44.279
It's the first and most abiding
maxim by which you practise by.

46:44.280 --> 46:47.029
And yet you have
done plenty, Captain.

46:47.030 --> 46:47.910
I've seen it.

46:47.911 --> 46:50.329
Only when sorely pressed
and never to a soul

46:50.330 --> 46:51.899
that didn't have it coming.

46:51.900 --> 46:54.509
You had a moral imperative.

46:54.510 --> 46:57.479
You want to call
it that, I did.

46:57.480 --> 46:58.919
This man, likewise.

46:58.920 --> 47:00.749
A child-- his child.

47:00.750 --> 47:04.709
No sin too great to
save her, I imagine.

47:04.710 --> 47:06.730
Perhaps you know
how he feels, Reid.

47:12.460 --> 47:15.080
Drum, I'm sure I saw a
bottle back here somewhere.

47:44.110 --> 47:46.419
You hope to get a little
reading, are you, Sergeant?

47:46.420 --> 47:47.579
Uh, no.

47:47.580 --> 47:49.749
Uh, I mean, well, yes.

47:49.750 --> 47:52.059
A bit of-- quiet moment.

47:52.060 --> 47:54.759
"Dracula."

47:54.760 --> 47:58.509
The evil Transylvanian Count.

47:58.510 --> 48:00.359
Because all foreigners
are dangerous

48:00.360 --> 48:04.350
predators set on the parasitic
cannibalism of our young women.

48:10.550 --> 48:15.099
I shall see this returned
then, shall I, Sergeant?

48:15.100 --> 48:21.229
Yes, I would-- um, uh,
uh, kind folk, Inspector.

48:21.230 --> 48:22.679
[TAPPING]

48:22.680 --> 48:24.619
Is that--

48:24.620 --> 48:25.829
It is, sir.

48:25.830 --> 48:26.680
French Police.

48:26.681 --> 48:27.949
There is a pursued felon, sir.

48:27.950 --> 48:29.119
Thus the urgency
of their response.

48:29.120 --> 48:30.649
And his crime?

48:30.650 --> 48:36.329
DRUM: His wife found bled
out in their Paris home

48:36.330 --> 48:38.649
and neither he nor their
daughter seen since.

48:38.650 --> 48:40.559
And his name, Drummond.

48:40.560 --> 48:41.769
[TAPPING]

48:41.770 --> 48:44.669
Blanchard, Tristram.

48:44.670 --> 48:45.490
48.

48:45.490 --> 48:46.430
His wife?

48:46.431 --> 48:48.549
Why would he perform the
same experiment on his wife?

48:48.550 --> 48:50.669
Perhaps she was sick, also.

48:50.670 --> 48:51.859
With the same disease.

48:51.860 --> 48:53.959
An inherited disease of
the blood-- haemophilia.

48:53.960 --> 48:55.939
Ah, that-- that can
be bad, but it can be

48:55.940 --> 48:57.299
managed with [INAUDIBLE] care.

48:57.300 --> 48:58.717
Worse than, rarer,
incurable even.

49:01.570 --> 49:03.729
[INAUDIBLE].

49:03.730 --> 49:05.359
It's a discoloration
of the teeth,

49:05.360 --> 49:08.139
anaemia, photosensitivity.

49:08.140 --> 49:10.399
Break down of the bones.

49:10.400 --> 49:13.009
One might consider it a moral
imperative to seek to spare

49:13.010 --> 49:16.219
a child from such suffering.

49:16.220 --> 49:18.009
Thatcher!

49:18.010 --> 49:19.589
How's your French, Sergeant?

49:19.590 --> 49:21.229
Uh, worse than my Polish, sir.

49:21.230 --> 49:22.509
Then simply shout louder.

49:22.510 --> 49:24.229
Get a [INAUDIBLE]
French Embassy.

49:24.230 --> 49:24.930
Wake them.

49:24.931 --> 49:26.299
Do not leave until
they have provided you

49:26.300 --> 49:28.299
with full, photographic
details of this man.

49:28.300 --> 49:29.300
Blanchard.

49:40.610 --> 49:41.610
Miss Dobrowski.

49:43.860 --> 49:46.890
I'm relieved to finally
meet you in person.

49:50.710 --> 49:53.569
I did not mean to
deceive you, sir.

49:53.570 --> 49:54.480
Before, I mean.

49:54.481 --> 49:58.829
When you sent another
in your name, hm?

49:58.830 --> 50:01.740
She who is now gone.

50:04.360 --> 50:06.199
I made a sacrifice
for a greater need.

50:06.200 --> 50:08.479
The only mercy is that
it was a final trial.

50:08.480 --> 50:12.559
Else you would now also have the
sacrifice of my daughter's life

50:12.560 --> 50:13.560
on your conscience.

50:21.470 --> 50:23.959
Your life transformed, hm?

50:23.960 --> 50:27.730
In return for the
transformation of my Camille.

50:43.190 --> 50:44.760
But you are here now.

50:47.920 --> 50:50.129
[INAUDIBLE].

50:50.130 --> 50:53.659
This is because
they are French.

50:53.660 --> 50:56.519
But as Mr. Reid
suggested, I shouted.

50:56.520 --> 50:59.679
And they soon packed
up their moaning.

50:59.680 --> 51:01.999
No, he's also down
to their being French.

51:02.000 --> 51:03.000
May I, Inspector?

51:09.290 --> 51:11.989
This man.

51:11.990 --> 51:13.410
I have met this man.

51:18.070 --> 51:21.090
It begins now, my Camille.
Hm?

51:31.570 --> 51:33.060
[GLASS BREAKING]

51:34.060 --> 51:36.560
- You'll need a [INAUDIBLE].
- [INAUDIBLE].

51:40.050 --> 51:41.550
[WHISPERING]

51:50.030 --> 51:51.529
Stop!

51:51.530 --> 51:54.009
We can't just go in there
thundering with our irons out.

51:54.010 --> 51:55.819
You tell us why not.

51:55.820 --> 51:56.989
What he does in
there is delicate.

51:56.990 --> 51:58.109
We jump in, it goes bad.

51:58.110 --> 51:59.499
They start to bleed
out, they won't stop.

51:59.500 --> 52:00.500
Understand?

52:02.910 --> 52:05.089
Let me talk to him, Drake.

52:05.090 --> 52:07.579
Surgeon to surgeon.

52:07.580 --> 52:08.580
Go.

52:17.050 --> 52:18.510
[DOOR OPENING]

52:20.950 --> 52:22.419
Has she lost consciousness yet?

52:22.420 --> 52:23.569
[DOOR CLOSING]

52:23.570 --> 52:25.449
Who are you?

52:25.450 --> 52:26.799
Hm?

52:26.800 --> 52:29.699
What do you want?

52:29.700 --> 52:30.899
Has the board of
this fine hospital

52:30.900 --> 52:33.869
approved the carrying out
of discredited medicine

52:33.870 --> 52:36.589
by fugitive outlaws?

52:36.590 --> 52:39.599
So you are police?

52:39.600 --> 52:40.630
Just another physician.

52:44.460 --> 52:47.879
Of sort.

52:47.880 --> 52:50.139
I performed the autopsy
on the other girl.

52:50.140 --> 52:53.929
Saw what catastrophe this
science caused to her organs.

52:53.930 --> 52:56.239
[MUMBLING]

52:56.240 --> 52:58.179
It's OK, darling.

52:58.180 --> 52:59.679
Shh, shh, shh.

52:59.680 --> 53:00.670
It's OK.

53:00.671 --> 53:01.849
Well, then you know, huh?

53:01.850 --> 53:06.979
Death was a result of, uh,
an opportunistic falsehood.

53:06.980 --> 53:09.939
This girl will come to no harm.

53:09.940 --> 53:12.629
You take all of her blood,
sir, she's going to die.

53:12.630 --> 53:15.920
Now I expect you didn't tell her
that when you struck this deal.

53:20.260 --> 53:22.679
- Who is this man, Father?
- No, no, no, no.

53:22.680 --> 53:23.640
Be still, my Camille.

53:23.641 --> 53:25.099
Be still now.

53:25.100 --> 53:28.109
You trust in me?

53:28.110 --> 53:29.549
Yes.

53:29.550 --> 53:30.550
Then rest.

53:33.380 --> 53:34.629
Close your eyes.

53:34.630 --> 53:36.449
You can't save her.

53:36.450 --> 53:38.129
You can't.

53:38.130 --> 53:40.119
Even if this transfusion
is completed,

53:40.120 --> 53:43.229
the symptoms will only
regress for a while.

53:43.230 --> 53:45.849
Whatever it is, there's
no way yet on earth

53:45.850 --> 53:48.789
found to alter those cards.

53:48.790 --> 53:49.730
No!

53:49.731 --> 53:53.729
You-- step back.

53:53.730 --> 53:54.680
What do you know?

53:54.681 --> 53:59.449
You judge me, but any
father would do the same.

53:59.450 --> 54:01.749
This is my life's work.

54:01.750 --> 54:03.019
She will recover.

54:03.020 --> 54:04.419
She will transform.

54:04.420 --> 54:05.929
She will live.

54:05.930 --> 54:06.920
Gentle sir.

54:06.921 --> 54:08.239
I beg you.

54:08.240 --> 54:09.340
Do not do this.

54:21.120 --> 54:22.370
As you wish, sir.

54:41.180 --> 54:42.170
Reid, Drake!

54:42.171 --> 54:43.649
Get in here!

54:43.650 --> 54:44.650
Get after him.

54:48.120 --> 54:49.949
Thatcher, you're with me.

54:49.950 --> 54:52.429
I need your help, man.

54:52.430 --> 54:54.409
There's too much blood.

54:54.410 --> 54:55.629
There's too much goddamn blood.

54:55.630 --> 54:57.359
We're going to try
a vessel ligation.

54:57.360 --> 54:58.370
Hand me those forceps.

55:02.630 --> 55:04.869
For Christ's take, man.
Right there.

55:04.870 --> 55:07.699
Forceps!

55:07.700 --> 55:10.059
Got it.

55:10.060 --> 55:14.279
If I can clamp the vessel,
that might buy us enough time.

55:14.280 --> 55:15.280
Come on, Magdalena.

55:19.160 --> 55:20.620
[CRASH]

55:21.880 --> 55:22.880
Stay back!

55:27.510 --> 55:30.579
How can I let her suffer?

55:30.580 --> 55:32.819
Without me, what
hope does she have?

55:32.820 --> 55:34.410
MAN: There is always hope, sir.

55:42.690 --> 55:44.149
No.

55:44.150 --> 55:47.759
In Heaven, she will know
the love of her mother.

55:47.760 --> 55:49.379
Such love, sir.

55:49.380 --> 55:53.969
All that you are-- put
to the protecting of her.

55:53.970 --> 55:55.810
I do not believe you
will now do this thing.

56:05.040 --> 56:06.040
Goddammit!

56:09.700 --> 56:11.189
It's too late.

56:11.190 --> 56:12.180
We lost too much.

56:12.180 --> 56:13.180
We lost her, Thatcher.

56:17.130 --> 56:18.609
No, no!
No.

56:18.610 --> 56:19.869
Look.

56:19.870 --> 56:21.209
Captain, take mine.

56:21.210 --> 56:22.060
Remember?

56:22.061 --> 56:24.299
If-- if I was-- if I was a
match for the hanging man,

56:24.300 --> 56:28.379
I'm also a match
for her, am I not?

56:28.380 --> 56:30.370
- Thatcher, you son of a bitch.
- Yeah.

56:33.370 --> 56:35.359
Hold tight, girl.

56:35.360 --> 56:37.360
Frankie Thatcher's
coming for you.

56:58.320 --> 56:59.310
[CRYING]

56:59.311 --> 57:02.699
My Camille.

57:02.700 --> 57:03.700
I have killed you.

57:07.640 --> 57:09.640
[CRYING]

57:30.420 --> 57:36.819
(SINGING) Little girl, little
girl, don't you lie to me.

57:36.820 --> 57:40.730
Tell me where did
you sleep last night?

57:43.470 --> 57:50.409
In the pines, in the pines,
in the cold lonesome pines.

57:50.410 --> 57:57.069
Will you shiver when
the cold wind blows.

57:57.070 --> 58:02.499
Little girl, little girl,
don't you lie to me.

58:02.500 --> 58:08.939
Tell me where did
you sleep last night?

58:08.940 --> 58:10.739
It is a song, Bennet.

58:10.740 --> 58:12.649
Only a song.

58:12.650 --> 58:14.979
And you launch such
conclusions at me.

58:14.980 --> 58:15.680
No, Rose.

58:15.681 --> 58:17.239
You think you can hide
such a truth from me.

58:17.240 --> 58:18.240
You cannot!

58:24.430 --> 58:25.420
How often?

58:25.421 --> 58:27.330
And do not think
to lie to me again.

58:30.760 --> 58:32.359
- Once a week.
- Oh, Jesus.

58:32.360 --> 58:33.170
In the month since.

58:33.171 --> 58:36.259
But it was not planned, Bennet.

58:36.260 --> 58:41.209
He found me all frantic with
the strain of it and helped us.

58:41.210 --> 58:44.149
Brought us home and--
and Connor-- he-- well,

58:44.150 --> 58:46.119
he calmed with him.

58:46.120 --> 58:47.080
[BABY COOING]

58:47.081 --> 58:48.979
And I could not deny him that.

58:48.980 --> 58:52.789
And does the boy--
does Connor know him?

58:52.790 --> 58:54.770
I mean, know who he is?

58:59.190 --> 59:02.769
You are the only father
he has ever known.

59:02.770 --> 59:06.049
The only father
he will ever know.

59:06.050 --> 59:07.490
[CRYING]

59:09.400 --> 59:10.839
No, no.

59:10.840 --> 59:11.840
I'll see to him.

59:15.300 --> 59:16.300
It's all right then.

59:18.880 --> 59:22.549
I'm here now.

59:22.550 --> 59:24.040
It's all right, [INAUDIBLE].

59:50.910 --> 59:53.759
- Is it that you do not like him?
- I barely know him.

59:53.760 --> 59:54.460
That is my point.

59:54.461 --> 59:58.179
Neither do you.

59:58.180 --> 59:59.759
And yet I like him.

59:59.760 --> 01:00:01.260
That-- that is a
guess, Mathilda.

01:00:05.390 --> 01:00:09.979
And so instead you would prefer
I created experiments to test

01:00:09.980 --> 01:00:11.529
what [INAUDIBLE] is made of.

01:00:11.530 --> 01:00:13.269
I might, yes.

01:00:13.270 --> 01:00:17.020
But do you not see
this is that experiment?

01:00:21.820 --> 01:00:23.909
He appreciates it the way
he does not appreciate it.

01:00:23.910 --> 01:00:26.029
These things are guides for you.

01:00:26.030 --> 01:00:28.919
Well, is that not fair?

01:00:28.920 --> 01:00:29.880
Fair?

01:00:29.881 --> 01:00:32.959
I'm not sure, Mathilda.

01:00:32.960 --> 01:00:36.889
When these human
transactions were writ,

01:00:36.890 --> 01:00:38.599
fairness was not much
of a consideration.

01:00:48.610 --> 01:00:51.169
You make your test, Mathilda.

01:00:51.170 --> 01:00:54.600
But be sure to let me
know if he passes or not.

01:01:39.010 --> 01:01:42.509
PROBYN: I, uh, served
for a time in Alexandria.

01:01:42.510 --> 01:01:45.589
Ah, and grew fond
of the blend there.

01:01:45.590 --> 01:01:47.339
Quite so.

01:01:47.340 --> 01:01:49.909
I was not, uh, misinformed then?

01:01:49.910 --> 01:01:52.089
You do have access
to the Egyptian

01:01:52.090 --> 01:01:54.529
brand of tobacco I favour?

01:01:54.530 --> 01:01:57.419
It has taken me an age
to hunt down a supply.

01:01:57.420 --> 01:01:58.420
[LAUGHS]

01:01:58.870 --> 01:02:01.239
Well, you may rest gentle, sir.

01:02:01.240 --> 01:02:03.309
That hunt is now behind you.

01:02:03.310 --> 01:02:04.689
Ah.

01:02:04.690 --> 01:02:06.059
Mister--

01:02:06.060 --> 01:02:07.410
WOMAN: His name's Probyn.

01:02:13.800 --> 01:02:17.029
Not a tobacconist?

01:02:17.030 --> 01:02:18.889
No.

01:02:18.890 --> 01:02:20.460
He is a doctor.
The Newgate doctor.

01:02:23.760 --> 01:02:27.009
I am relieved of my
duties now, however.

01:02:27.010 --> 01:02:28.689
How have you found me?

01:02:28.690 --> 01:02:30.279
How?

01:02:30.280 --> 01:02:32.589
I am shocked you asked.

01:02:32.590 --> 01:02:35.159
That husband of yours
stalking back into my life

01:02:35.160 --> 01:02:36.179
with his threats.

01:02:36.180 --> 01:02:38.899
It is his colleague
has me reported

01:02:38.900 --> 01:02:41.449
and deprived of my work.

01:02:41.450 --> 01:02:43.759
200 pounds.

01:02:43.760 --> 01:02:46.979
Otherwise, my own
further harm or know,

01:02:46.980 --> 01:02:50.809
your secret will be told
and that wretch son of yours

01:02:50.810 --> 01:02:54.279
will never see your
spiteful little face again.

01:02:54.280 --> 01:02:56.819
Abel, I think, on
reflection, you should not.

01:02:56.820 --> 01:02:59.329
ABEL: For why?

01:02:59.330 --> 01:03:02.769
[INAUDIBLE] had his sack
of [INAUDIBLE] this one.

01:03:02.770 --> 01:03:04.589
No threat [INAUDIBLE],
and I cannot

01:03:04.590 --> 01:03:07.269
believe he will be missed.

01:03:07.270 --> 01:03:08.790
I shall tell you for why, Abel.

01:03:16.630 --> 01:03:18.970
Between first and
second rib, is it not?

01:03:22.600 --> 01:03:24.230
It is, my dear.

01:03:28.500 --> 01:03:29.500
Oh.

01:03:41.130 --> 01:03:42.130
[GASP]

01:03:44.110 --> 01:03:49.309
Nate, two ox and a
tarpaulin, if you please.

01:03:49.310 --> 01:03:51.210
Speak to me of
my son, would you?

01:03:55.020 --> 01:03:57.340
Eh?
Yes, yes.

01:03:59.500 --> 01:04:00.500
Brandy.

01:04:04.180 --> 01:04:06.509
There.

01:04:06.510 --> 01:04:08.989
Fit for a king.

01:04:08.990 --> 01:04:12.600
Had the French not done away
with such things as kings.

01:04:26.560 --> 01:04:29.249
What am I, Abel?

01:04:29.250 --> 01:04:31.250
Why, a princess.

01:04:34.320 --> 01:04:37.289
Oh, no.

01:04:37.290 --> 01:04:38.729
Why do you weep?

01:04:38.730 --> 01:04:40.219
Not for him, surely.

01:04:40.220 --> 01:04:41.200
[CRYING]

01:04:41.201 --> 01:04:44.139
No.

01:04:44.140 --> 01:04:47.079
The other.

01:04:47.080 --> 01:04:48.310
The dark secret I spoke of.

01:04:49.370 --> 01:04:50.070
Ah.

01:04:50.071 --> 01:04:52.570
The last definite
death by my hand.

01:04:56.670 --> 01:04:57.670
And who he?

01:05:01.890 --> 01:05:04.699
My father.

01:05:04.700 --> 01:05:07.099
It was my father.

01:05:07.100 --> 01:05:08.599
I killed my father.

